headline: How the CyberArk Story Is Shifting as Analysts Weigh Palo Alto Networks Acquisition
summary: CyberArk Software’s consensus analyst price target has edged upward, moving from $462.53 to $470.27, as coverage intensifies amid acquisition news. This shift comes as analysts react to the anticipated synergy and growth potential created by the pending Palo Alto Networks takeover. At the same time, some note possible limits to further upside.
